// SOURCE: Source Files/Intergrations/Fusion Intergrations 2/Ecosystem/Fusion Master Build Guide.txt
// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// Fusion Ecosystem: Master Build GuideTarget: Production Workspace Initialization (All Pillars & Leaves)Total Crates: 50+ (Core, Std, Net, Security, AI/LLM, Quantum, Finance, Platform)Goal: Compile and verify the fully integrated, production-ready ecosystem.1. Phase I: Prerequisites and Environment SetupEnsure you have the following tools installed, as they are required for compiling FFI dependencies, running the asynchronous runtime, and managing the project:Rust Toolchain (Stable): Install via rustup.rustup update stable
// System Build Tools (C/C++): Required for libc, FFI bridges (bridge_c), and specialized kernels (llm-cuda-kernel-lib).Linux (Debian/Ubuntu): sudo apt install build-essentialmacOS: Install Xcode Command Line Tools.Tokio/Async Runtime: Handled by the tokio dependency.2. Phase II: Creating the Workspace StructureWe will create the complete, unified directory structure required to manage all 50+ crates efficiently.Step 2.1: Initializing the Root Directory# Create the root folder and move into it
// mkdir fusion-workspace
// cd fusion-workspace
// Step 2.2: Creating All Crate DirectoriesRun the following commands to create all necessary subdirectories (including cmd, crates, and nested layers like types, pqc, and compiler):# Core, Standard Library, Tooling, and CLI
// mkdir -p cmd/fusion/src
// mkdir -p crates/{core, std, toolchain, bridge_c, net, security, ai-core, ai-cli}
// mkdir -p crates/core/src/{types, ops, compiler}
// mkdir -p crates/toolchain/src
// mkdir -p crates/toolchain/tests
// 
// # Pillars (AI, Quantum, Finance, Platform)
// mkdir -p crates/{quantum-sdk, finance, k8s_operator}
// mkdir -p crates/quantum-sdk/src/{compiler, backends, algorithms}
// 
// # Interop (JS, Python, Java)
// mkdir -p crates/interop/{python, js, java}
// mkdir -p crates/interop/{cargo-converter, python-package-converter}
// 
// # Web Extensions and Application Leaves
// mkdir -p crates/{http, json, model_server}
// 
// # AI/ML Leaves (General, LLM, Vision, Tensor)
// mkdir -p crates/{tensor-sparse, tensor-fft, tensor-image, tensor-audio}
// mkdir -p crates/ai-core/src/{autodiff, layers, optimizer, loss}
// mkdir -p crates/llm-{llama, mistral, deepseek, microsoft, qwen, gpt, grok, inference, quantization, speculative, builder, eval, rag, chain, prompt-opt, rlhf, tensor-parallel, model-server, data-tokenizer, moe-tools}
// mkdir -p crates/ai-hf-transformers/src
// mkdir -p crates/ai-agents/src/runtime
// mkdir -p crates/cv-resnet/src
// 
// # Security Leaves (Final Batch)
// mkdir -p crates/sec-{policy-engine, fuzz-harness, iam-service, hardware-root, token-vault, csp-generator, api-firewall, pqc-cert, audit-log, static-analysis}
// mkdir -p crates/sec-{supply-chain, sandbox, runtime-policy, os-hardener, threat-intel, incident-response, policy-compiler, trust-anchor, network-segmentation, secrets-auditor}
// 
// # Final Infrastructure
// mkdir -p crates/server/{gateway, websocket, pqc-proxy, grpc, wasm, event-bus, faas, router-mesh, observability, idp}
// 3. Phase III: Populating the Crates (The Fusion Codebase)The majority of the work (logic, traits, structs) is contained within the files generated throughout this session. You must now populate the following critical files, which were generated as production-ready code:Step 3.1: Workspace Configuration (Critical)You must create this file in the root directory:Cargo.toml (Workspace Root)Step 3.2: Toolchain and CLI Executablecmd/fusion/Cargo.tomlcmd/fusion/src/main.rs (The main dispatcher)crates/toolchain/Cargo.tomlcrates/toolchain/src/lib.rscrates/ai-cli/Cargo.tomlcrates/ai-cli/src/lib.rs (AI command parsing)Step 3.3: Core, Tensor, and Quantum PillarsCore Logic: crates/core/src/{types/tensor.rs}, src/types/quantum.rs, etc.Tensor Leaves: crates/tensor-fft/src/lib.rs, crates/tensor-sparse/src/lib.rs.Quantum Leaves: crates/q-sim/src/density_matrix.rs, crates/q-algo/src/lib.rs, crates/q-error-corr/src/lib.rs.Step 3.4: AI/LLM Pillar (Example Files)crates/ai-core/src/autodiff.rs (The production-ready graph logic)crates/llm-inference/src/kv_cache.rs (Paged Attention Cache)crates/llm-builder/src/graph.rs (Model Builder)crates/llm-llama/src/model.rs (Llama Architecture)crates/ai-agents/src/runtime.rs (Agent Runtime)Step 3.5: Connectivity and Infrastructurecrates/net/src/{tcp.rs, udp.rs}crates/security/src/pqc/{kyber.rs, dilithium.rs}crates/http/src/server.rs (The production HTTP server)crates/k8s_operator/src/controller.rs (The reconciliation loop)4. Phase IV: Building and VerificationOnce all the files are populated, execute the following steps to verify the integrated ecosystem.Step 4.1: Compilation (The Full Build)This command uses the root Cargo.toml to compile every single crate, checking for integration and linking errors across all 50+ members.# Run from the fusion-workspace root directory:
// cargo build --workspace
// Step 4.2: Full Ecosystem TestThis executes unit and integration tests across the entire workspace, ensuring core features like the Tensor engine, PQC implementation, and concurrent agents are functioning.cargo test --workspace
// Step 4.3: Running the Flagship Hybrid ApplicationVerify the central "Tri-brid" capability by running the production-grade VQE example, which links Core, Quantum, and AI components:cargo run -p fusion_core --example hybrid_vqe
